Red Tide Update: Concentrations Decrease in Pinela, Manati and Sarasota Provinces
The latest announcement from the Florida Fish and Wildlife Commission shows a general fall in Red Tide concentrations for parts of the Tampa Bay region.
According to the FWC, conditions of uneven spots are observed in areas of Pinela, Manati, Sarasota, Charlotte and Colier provinces, which suggest a decrease in concentrations.
A spot of the Red Tide extends to about 130 miles of coastline from the northern Pinela province to the southern province of Li.
Spots are spotted about 10 miles off the Hillsborough coast, but in fewer places than last week.
The Red Tide has also been observed in the Pasco province.
Moderate concentrations were recorded on the coast and off the coast of the Pinela Province last week, low to high concentrations were recorded off the coast in Hillsborough Province, background to high concentrations in Manati Province, background to high concentrations on the coast or off the coast in Sarasota Province, background to moderate concentrations in Charlotte Province, background to high concentrations on the coast or off the coast in Li province and low concentrations in Colier province.
Respiratory disturbances continue to be recorded in the provinces of Pinela, Manati, Sarasota, Lee and Colierre.
No respiratory disturbances were reported in the northwest Florida in the last week.
